Crystal Reports to Power BI is not a conversion — it’s a modernization.
Power BI requires:
A new data model, Rewritten queries ,Rebuilt visuals, Translated formulas
We can  reuse the logic, not the files

What We Can Reuse
Existing SQL queries embedded in Crystal .rpt files (business logic, joins, filters).
All underlying data sources and database structures.
Business rules, formulas, and grouping logic, these need to be translated into DAX
Report parameters and filtering logic which needs to be mapped to Power BI slicers/filters
Report output requirements can stay the same (PDF)

What Must Be Rebuilt
Work with business for report layouts and visualizations as Power BI uses interactive visuals
Rewrite Crystal formulas in DAX or Power Query
Rewrite A centralized Power BI semantic model as Crystal has no shared model
Author embedding layer inside the ASP.NET Core application - follow TTC best practices

My recommendation (for this release)
Use Power BI Paginated Reports, for PDF output, which will be similar like existing PDF reports
Deploy dashboards and analytics after PDF reports are generated (do business like to see the reports in dashboards with nice UI)?
